The paper discusses Inductive Logic Programming (ILP) and cost-sensitive classification, which are both topics commonly found in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Prolog programming language also suggests a possible fit in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The competition aspect of the paper may also make it relevant to the Data Mining (cs.DM) sub-category. Finally, the analysis of the results and algorithm development may also make it relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
